    dc:description "FIG. 6. — Atlantapseudes cyanea n. sp.: A, holotype ♀, dorsal; B, antennule; C, antenna; D, labrum; E, left mandible; F, detail of margin of molar process of left mandible;G, lacinia mobilis of right mandible; H, labium; I, maxillule; J, epignath. Scale bar: A, 2 mm; B, C, 0.6 mm; D-J, 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5394177/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5394179>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. — Atlantapseudes cyanea n. sp.: A, maxilliped and endite;B, chela; C-G, pereopods 1-3, 5 and 6 respectively;H, distal articles of pereopod 6. Scale bar: A, 0.3 mm; B-G, 0.6 mm; H, 0.15 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5394179/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

